this last convoy arrived from Rott att hull without your knowdledge
& that of your packs be brought over is a wriddle for mee, now have advise
from Rott that an other convoj was gon for hull 10 dayes agoe where op
the french capers have taken some ships, so thatt itt zeems those of
Rott are vere malheurous, & not able to defend their merchand men
& oors gives meerea this gives mee reason to belive, that they must
make aturne for schotland, so that those of Amst will be the first
departing wherefore shipt by them the 5 packs of which I have
invoyce & the rest which you are approveidinge for Rott the more
belause the Amst hath 3 men of warr, so hope that this shall come
in time to have them 5 packs shipped that way, though my last is order
enongh so to doe, the mere if you finde that the rott convoj was departed
& whiich sence arrived att hull perhaps butt 1 of 2 men of warr, that I
writt you the 5 past to ship butt 3 packs for Amst, when that convoy
should depart first, was because I looked upon that convoy last arrived
att Rott to consist of 4 ships & sence that is arrived & that of Amst
now there & of 3 ships, so wish att leastt 5 a 6 packs aboard these for
I question not, butt that you have readdy by this tome one pack more of
kersies & one of cloth, which to ship for Rott, now I hope you
shall observe what you are a proveidinge att london to ship some span
clothes for holland principally those ordered 12 past & rather for Amst
then Rott all the rest for the first convoij for ostend, this beeng the
needfull att present rest
